WEBVTT

00:13.012 --> 00:15.015
[hip-hop music playing]

00:17.142 --> 00:20.520
<i>♪ One, two, one, two, three ♪</i>

00:20.603 --> 00:22.814
<i>♪ Where Brooklyn at?</i>
<i>Where Brooklyn at? ♪</i>

00:22.897 --> 00:24.816
<i>♪ Where Brooklyn at?</i>
<i>Where Brooklyn at? ♪</i>

00:28.820 --> 00:32.032
[soft piano music plays]

01:03.938 --> 01:06.816
<i>♪ Take me to a place</i>
<i>Take me to a place ♪</i>

01:06.900 --> 01:13.740
Sometimes, being this good-looking...
can be a burden. Oh, yeah.

01:16.201 --> 01:17.577
But I'm used to it.

01:20.205 --> 01:25.710
Nola and I met a year ago.
I saw her eyeing me.

01:27.629 --> 01:29.422
And she wasn't even interested.

01:30.131 --> 01:33.384
And that... was a big turn-on.

01:34.219 --> 01:37.222
And I've been turnin' her out ever since.

01:37.305 --> 01:40.809
As Nola likes to say,
we are "fuck buddies,"

01:40.892 --> 01:43.895
and with that comes "fuck buddy" codes.

01:44.437 --> 01:48.483
She has her rules.
We don't really hang out.

01:48.566 --> 01:51.528
We can't say we're exclusive.

01:52.487 --> 01:54.364
But that's about to change.

01:54.447 --> 01:58.326
Last night, at the gallery,
I saw a different side of Nola Darling.

01:58.868 --> 02:03.790
Now, I see more than just her body.
I see the woman inside.

02:04.415 --> 02:10.213
I saw a Nola in her world,
a woman in her element, self-possessed.

02:10.296 --> 02:13.216
She is special.

02:13.299 --> 02:16.344
Hey, it's one thing fuckin' her
in her lovin' bed.

02:16.427 --> 02:19.389
But it's another
bein' in the real world together.

02:20.723 --> 02:23.768
I know she's got those dudes
she hangs with.

02:24.561 --> 02:28.064
Their punk-asses were probably orbiting
around her show last night.

02:28.857 --> 02:30.859
But I didn't see any competition.

02:32.360 --> 02:36.489
Except for maybe that woman, Opal.

02:38.575 --> 02:41.911
Okay, you got me.
I'm not used to workin' this hard.

02:43.121 --> 02:44.956
But I'm up for the challenge.

02:45.999 --> 02:49.544
People,
I came out of my dear mother's womb ready.

02:51.629 --> 02:54.883
Why wouldn't she... wanna be with me?

02:56.426 --> 02:58.553
I am a great fuckin' catch.

03:01.431 --> 03:06.394
That's it.
Today, I'm breakin' those rules.

03:06.477 --> 03:08.479
[soft R&B song plays]

03:12.984 --> 03:14.360
[sighs] Okay.

03:19.324 --> 03:21.576
[crowd cheering]

03:21.659 --> 03:23.703
Ahh! Damn.

03:25.163 --> 03:28.416
<i>I am bursting with excitement.</i>

03:28.499 --> 03:33.171
I want to howl like a wolf!
[howls, chuckles]

03:33.254 --> 03:38.718
<i>An outstanding group show</i>
<i>curated by the talented Clorinda Bradford</i>

03:39.260 --> 03:42.555
<i>opened last night</i>
<i>at the New Medina Gallery in Dumbo.</i>

03:42.639 --> 03:46.851
First, of course,
we have the Haitian sensation, Baptiste...

03:47.560 --> 03:49.520
[faster]
...<i>whose meaty-textured black on black</i>

03:49.604 --> 03:51.856
<i>-eliminates the need for shade, line...</i>
-Blah, blah, blah.

03:51.940 --> 03:54.484
<i>-by bathing the eye in the infinity...</i>
-Skip.

03:54.567 --> 03:58.279
-Zora Kneel Hurtin' subverts pop art...
-Enough already!

03:58.363 --> 04:00.448
[fast]<i> ...re-purposing</i>
<i>Madam C.J. Walker's hot comb,</i>

04:00.531 --> 04:03.243
<i>and thus, sets fire to the items</i>
<i>that have shackled the souls...</i>

04:03.326 --> 04:05.995
<i>Lemuel Richards excretes blackness</i>
<i>in every stroke of his pen.</i>

04:06.079 --> 04:09.165
-You don't get it? He doesn't give a fuck!
-Ahh!

04:09.249 --> 04:11.459
<i>The viewer must rise</i>
<i>to meet him in blackness.</i>

04:11.542 --> 04:14.254
...the problem of the show
and its weakest link, Nola Darling.

04:14.337 --> 04:15.213
[gasps]

04:15.296 --> 04:17.006
[rewinding]

04:17.090 --> 04:21.511
<i>And that brings me to the problem</i>
<i>of the show and its weakest link,</i>

04:21.594 --> 04:23.805
<i>Nola Darling.</i>

04:23.888 --> 04:25.807
<i>You heard right the first time.</i>

04:25.890 --> 04:28.726
You, Nola Darling, are the weakest link.

04:28.810 --> 04:32.021
Ms. Darling's work is almost out of place

04:32.105 --> 04:37.443
and overshadowed by the fierce trifecta
of African-American artists.

04:37.527 --> 04:40.029
-Ahh!
<i>-Her selection of work is pedestrian</i>

04:40.113 --> 04:43.241
<i>when compared to the electrifying</i>
<i>political perspectives of her peers.</i>

04:43.324 --> 04:45.785
-Fast forward. [gasps]
<i>-Stop fast-forwarding.</i>

04:45.868 --> 04:49.122
Now, I had the opportunity
to talk with Ms. Darling

04:49.205 --> 04:53.960
about her selection of works,
which she has presumptively entitled,

04:54.460 --> 04:57.297
<i>The Free Female Black Form.</i>

04:57.380 --> 05:01.509
And she was decidedly unable
to articulate its meaning

05:01.592 --> 05:02.802
<i>-in any cohesive manner.</i>
-Fuck!

05:02.885 --> 05:05.471
And is there any surprise in that?

05:05.555 --> 05:10.852
How can one encapsulate
the free female black form?

05:10.935 --> 05:15.189
<i>To her credit,</i>
<i>Ms. Darling has ample facility.</i>

05:15.273 --> 05:19.402
<i>It's certainly not a question</i>
<i>of talent or skill, not by any means.</i>

05:19.485 --> 05:20.486
Oh, thanks.

05:20.570 --> 05:25.616
<i>Perhaps, her artistic eyes</i>
<i>were just bigger than her stomach.</i>

05:25.700 --> 05:27.243
<i>Let's be frank.</i>

05:27.327 --> 05:31.122
<i>Not quite working with the same intensity</i>
<i>as her diastopian peers</i>

05:31.205 --> 05:33.916
<i>and with no unifying principles,</i>

05:34.000 --> 05:35.835
<i>Ms. Darling's selection of work</i>

05:35.918 --> 05:41.591
<i>is disparate, disjointed, diluted,</i>
<i>and dysfunctional.</i>

05:42.717 --> 05:46.179
<i>I don't want to know</i>
<i>who Ms. Darling is inspired by.</i>

05:46.262 --> 05:51.059
I want to know who she is.

05:51.434 --> 05:53.019
Fuck you, Julius Kemper!

05:53.644 --> 05:56.105
[soft jazz music playing]

05:56.189 --> 05:57.148
Shit!

05:57.231 --> 05:59.859
-[phone beeps]
-[Greer] <i>Bonjour, Mademoiselle Nola.</i>

05:59.942 --> 06:01.444
C'est moi<i>, Greer.</i>

06:02.028 --> 06:04.030
Chérie, félicitations.

06:04.113 --> 06:05.448
<i>-Call me back.</i>
-[phone beeps]

06:05.531 --> 06:08.284
[Septima] <i>Ladybug,</i>
<i>this is Mommy and Daddy calling.</i>

06:08.367 --> 06:09.994
<i>We are so proud of you.</i>

06:10.078 --> 06:12.330
<i>Your father's making</i>
<i>your favorite greasy breakfast,</i>

06:12.413 --> 06:15.291
<i>some salmon croquettes,</i>
<i>some grits and potatoes.</i>

06:15.374 --> 06:17.043
<i>-Mm! Stop by.</i>
-[phone beeps]

06:17.126 --> 06:20.171
[Jamie] <i>Nola, I hope my presence</i>
<i>was a pleasant surprise.</i>

06:20.254 --> 06:22.006
<i>I promise, it won't be the last.</i>

06:22.548 --> 06:23.841
<i>-Hit me back.</i>
-[phone beeps]

06:23.925 --> 06:27.220
-[Greer] <i>Nola, </i>chérie<i>, call me back.</i>
-[phone beeps]

06:27.303 --> 06:30.765
[Opal, Skylar] <i>Money is coming!</i>
<i>Money is coming! Money is coming!</i>

06:30.848 --> 06:32.767
-[phone beeps]
-[Mars] <i>Yo, yo, yo!</i>

06:32.850 --> 06:35.770
<i> Nola, what up?</i>
<i>I ain't mad at you for not invitin' me.</i>

06:35.853 --> 06:39.190
<i>Hope you ain't mad at the kid for</i>
<i>standin' up for his femme fatale, a'ight?</i>

06:39.273 --> 06:42.485
<i>On the sincerious tip,</i>
<i>how about a make-up call?</i>

06:42.568 --> 06:44.320
<i>-Love from the planet Mars.</i>
-[phone beeps]

06:49.659 --> 06:50.493
[knocking on door]

06:52.286 --> 06:53.121
Come in.

06:55.289 --> 06:56.124
How are you?

06:56.916 --> 06:59.168
-Fine. You?
-Fine.

06:59.252 --> 07:03.214
Must be important for you to walk
all the way down here, to my dungeon.

07:03.297 --> 07:07.218
In fact, it's very important.
Virgil wants to play us something.

07:08.469 --> 07:10.638
-How is our son doing?
-Great.

07:11.597 --> 07:13.433
But you need to ask him yourself.

07:14.016 --> 07:14.851
Yeah.

07:15.560 --> 07:21.107
[playing "The Star-Spangled Banner"]

08:28.090 --> 08:29.926
[laughs]

08:31.010 --> 08:33.471
-[Cheryl] Bravo!
-[Jamie] Bravo!

08:33.971 --> 08:35.556
Come here. Give me a kiss.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.016
Wow!

08:38.142 --> 08:39.477
Where did that come from?

08:39.560 --> 08:41.729
It came from that stupid video I was in.

08:41.812 --> 08:44.398
I thought about who I am
and what this country's all about.

08:44.482 --> 08:48.736
I did some research and found out
Francis Scott Key wrote a mad racist verse

08:48.819 --> 08:50.404
endorsing slavery.

08:51.113 --> 08:54.075
So, all this time, we've been singing
this national anthem

08:54.158 --> 08:58.120
about our 246 years of enslavement,
not to end it, but to continue it.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.581
-Virgil, I didn't know this.
-Me neither.

09:00.957 --> 09:01.874
Google.

09:02.625 --> 09:04.126
All right, we'll be up soon.

09:04.585 --> 09:06.128
-That was great.
-Thank you.

09:06.212 --> 09:07.838
-Love you.
-Love you too.

09:11.050 --> 09:12.552
That's our best work.

09:13.678 --> 09:14.679
Yeah.

09:14.762 --> 09:18.182
Where is No-No La-La?

09:19.100 --> 09:20.851
La-No? La-No?

09:23.229 --> 09:27.733
[doorbell ringing]

09:27.984 --> 09:31.571
-[moans]
-[doorbell ringing]

09:32.280 --> 09:34.198
Ugh! Who is it?

09:34.282 --> 09:36.367
-[static]
-[man] <i>You know who this is.</i>

09:37.785 --> 09:39.203
I can't hear you!

09:40.079 --> 09:43.833
<i>-It's...</i>
-[doorbell ringing]

09:43.916 --> 09:45.918
Stop ringing my bell! Go away!

09:46.002 --> 09:48.254
[doorbell ringing]

09:48.337 --> 09:55.136
[ringing continues]

09:55.219 --> 09:56.053
Enough.

09:58.347 --> 09:59.724
-[grunts]
-[ringing stops]

09:59.807 --> 10:00.641
[sighs]

10:05.062 --> 10:09.191
-[knocking on door]
-[screams, whines]

10:12.194 --> 10:14.322
Are you fucking kidding me?

10:14.405 --> 10:16.657
[knocking continues]

10:20.828 --> 10:21.912
Go to hell!

10:23.039 --> 10:23.873
[door opens]

10:26.417 --> 10:28.544
What the fuck are you doing here, Greer?

10:29.545 --> 10:32.048
Somebody had a long night.
You gonna let me in?

10:32.506 --> 10:35.468
No! No, I'm not gonna let you in,

10:35.551 --> 10:38.304
and I do not appreciate you
coming over here unannounced.

10:38.387 --> 10:40.723
Well, if you would've answered
my calls and texts!

10:41.223 --> 10:42.224
Boy, bye!

10:46.228 --> 10:51.525
Baby, could you please open the door
so I can talk to you?

10:57.073 --> 11:00.660
Did I not set the rules?
And did you not agree to those rules?

11:00.743 --> 11:03.329
-All you do is break the rules.
-Whatever.

11:03.412 --> 11:08.250
-I'm not in the mood for a booty call.
-No, I'm not here for your lovin' bed.

11:08.334 --> 11:11.295
Let's go out,
celebrate your triumphant debut.

11:11.379 --> 11:14.215
How about dinner?
Go to a film. Whatever you like.

11:14.298 --> 11:19.887
I just wanna show you a nice time.
Cinema? Okay. Old or new?

11:19.970 --> 11:24.767
-Old. Shot in black-and-white.
-Okay, a film it is. I'll text you.

11:25.893 --> 11:27.395
I did not commit to that.

11:31.023 --> 11:33.776
[soft jazz music playing]

11:54.672 --> 11:55.798
[Greer] Mmm.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.217
Come on, I don't wanna miss previews.

11:59.593 --> 12:01.387
-Give me one of those.
-Yes.

12:13.107 --> 12:14.316
What can I do for you?

12:15.734 --> 12:16.819
Peola.

12:17.862 --> 12:19.905
We've been lookin' everywhere for you.

12:21.282 --> 12:22.616
Are you talking to me?

12:23.826 --> 12:26.745
There must be some mistake.
My name isn't Peola.

12:27.496 --> 12:30.875
There ain't no mistake.
Why have you got this job?

12:30.958 --> 12:34.044
You don't have to work.
I'll give you everything you want.

12:34.128 --> 12:36.130
What are you talking about?

12:36.213 --> 12:38.924
I'm sure you've got me confused
with someone else.

12:42.762 --> 12:47.099
Why, why, Peola, child, I'm your mammy.

12:47.683 --> 12:51.312
Why, that's ridiculous.
I never saw you before in my life.

12:51.395 --> 12:52.938
[man] What's the meaning of this?

12:53.022 --> 12:55.024
This woman doesn't know
what she's talking about.

12:57.276 --> 12:58.777
Do I look like her daughter?

13:01.655 --> 13:03.908
Do I look like I could be her daughter?

13:05.367 --> 13:06.952
Why, she must be crazy!

13:07.036 --> 13:08.537
[soft jazz music playing]

13:08.621 --> 13:09.622
You okay?

13:10.664 --> 13:11.582
Yeah, I'm fine.

13:16.587 --> 13:17.588
You got that...

13:18.506 --> 13:19.673
I don't know, this...

13:21.091 --> 13:22.676
<i>je ne sais quoi.</i>

13:24.929 --> 13:25.763
In fact...

13:27.890 --> 13:30.059
-Let me show you.
-Uh, I'm really--

13:30.142 --> 13:33.312
-Just get over here.
-[camera clicks]

13:37.107 --> 13:38.817
-That's sweet.
-Mm.

13:41.695 --> 13:42.530
<i>Bisou.</i>

13:58.587 --> 14:01.590
-Greer, lost my number?
-I miss you.

14:01.674 --> 14:04.426
-How you doin'?
-Long time no see.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.262
-Greer!
-Call me back.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.430
-[pop song playing]
-Where you been?

14:08.931 --> 14:11.642
<i>♪ Just for you to go and destroy it ♪</i>

14:12.726 --> 14:14.645
<i>♪ But that's just how it goes ♪</i>

14:16.063 --> 14:17.898
<i>♪ When your life isn't movin' ♪</i>

14:17.982 --> 14:19.108
[in French]

14:19.191 --> 14:20.818
[in French]

14:23.821 --> 14:24.822
<i>Salut.</i>

14:26.365 --> 14:28.659
<i>♪ Before you came, it was all about ♪</i>

14:28.742 --> 14:29.577
Thank you.

14:30.578 --> 14:32.788
<i>♪ All about, all about me ♪</i>

14:33.372 --> 14:36.876
<i>♪ I didn't worry about a thing ♪</i>

14:36.959 --> 14:39.795
<i>♪ 'Cause it was all about</i>
<i>All about me ♪</i>

14:40.462 --> 14:43.132
<i>♪ It's crazy</i>
<i>How you give your heart to someone ♪</i>

14:43.215 --> 14:46.343
<i>♪ Just to try somethin' different</i>
<i>Put your heart to a gun... ♪</i>

14:46.427 --> 14:48.345
-Problem?
-Not mine.

14:49.346 --> 14:51.682
-May I join you?
-Yes, please do.

14:52.433 --> 14:55.603
Nola, Lilly. Lilly, Nola.

14:55.686 --> 14:58.147
-You're beautiful.
-Thank you. So are you.

14:58.230 --> 15:00.608
[in French]

15:16.707 --> 15:18.751
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

15:19.293 --> 15:22.212
-I'll be back with your drink orders.
-Thank you.

15:22.296 --> 15:25.299
So, what, you think you're Guido
from Fellini's <i>8 1/2</i>?

15:26.467 --> 15:29.178
You got your harem at last, King Solomon.

15:29.261 --> 15:31.263
-[camera shutter clicking]
-[moaning]

15:31.889 --> 15:32.723
[in French]

15:33.098 --> 15:35.351
Anyway... [in French]

15:35.434 --> 15:37.937
Ooh, la, la.

15:38.020 --> 15:39.605
[in French]

15:40.189 --> 15:42.441
-You speak French now.
-Maybe.

15:42.524 --> 15:44.276
The language of love.

15:44.860 --> 15:48.113
Your accent... is so wack.

15:48.197 --> 15:49.490
[Greer laughs]

15:50.074 --> 15:52.284
-It's cute. It's cute.
-Don't touch me.

15:52.368 --> 15:53.869
[Greer laughs]

15:53.953 --> 15:59.083
I want you to try some
of these vegan dishes. It's my cheat day.

15:59.166 --> 16:03.253
This is fennel sausage.
This... is adzuki bacon.

16:04.338 --> 16:05.339
It's all beans.

16:06.590 --> 16:08.759
That is really good.
I've never had that before.

16:08.842 --> 16:09.677
Mm.

16:10.803 --> 16:13.847
I don't mind vegetarian,
but I'm an omnivore.

16:15.599 --> 16:19.687
Well, I may be a vegetarian,
but I'm a carnivore in your lovin' bed.

16:19.770 --> 16:22.523
You are a cannibal in my lovin' bed.

16:23.357 --> 16:25.609
[both growl, laugh]

16:25.693 --> 16:27.486
[phone vibrating]

16:32.157 --> 16:33.075
[in French]

16:33.158 --> 16:35.536
And congratulations on your show.

16:35.619 --> 16:36.996
<i>Superbe.</i>

16:37.079 --> 16:38.414
Thank you.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.835
-["All in Love is Fair" plays]
<i>-♪ All is fair in love ♪</i>

16:42.918 --> 16:48.257
Parent-teacher conferences are
next Thursday. Do you wanna go or shall I?

16:48.340 --> 16:50.801
As long as that white liberal asshole
headmaster is there...

16:50.884 --> 16:51.885
That's fine, I'll go.

16:51.969 --> 16:54.972
I'll go. It's not what I said.
If he's not there...

16:55.055 --> 16:56.015
No, it's fine.

16:56.098 --> 16:57.850
-I can go.
-I'm happy to go.

17:02.354 --> 17:07.818
<i>♪ In love as one they say ♪</i>

17:09.778 --> 17:16.076
<i>♪ But all is changed with time ♪</i>

17:16.785 --> 17:23.709
<i>♪ The future no one can see ♪</i>

17:24.043 --> 17:25.544
I told my wife and my son

17:25.627 --> 17:28.464
that I would never leave them
like my father left my mother and I.

17:29.548 --> 17:30.549
I'm stuck.

17:32.134 --> 17:33.886
Love versus duty.

17:34.553 --> 17:36.096
Passion over security.

17:36.847 --> 17:41.727
I need Nola Darling,
but my family needs me more.

17:43.020 --> 17:45.564
There's a poetry in this dilemma.

17:46.732 --> 17:50.110
But it's a poem that I wish
I could write my way out of.

17:52.196 --> 17:55.616
Can I evolve? Give it all up for Nola?

17:56.950 --> 17:59.703
Or make it work
with my beautiful wife, Cheryl?

18:00.287 --> 18:02.164
Why did I buy this self-portrait?

18:02.706 --> 18:05.542
If only it were Nola herself in my bed...

18:05.626 --> 18:08.253
It might be the only thing about Nola
I can afford.

18:09.880 --> 18:14.134
I grip it tight with the hand
that wears our wedding ring.

18:18.388 --> 18:20.140
This canvas is cold.

18:20.891 --> 18:22.518
This bed is colder.

18:23.977 --> 18:26.230
How can I spend another cold night alone?

18:30.359 --> 18:31.568
Quite a turnout last night.

18:31.652 --> 18:33.821
-How do you think it went?
-It went well.

18:34.446 --> 18:35.906
I was in good company.

18:36.323 --> 18:40.410
It was a bit nerve-wracking at first,
but I was happy to be a part of it.

18:40.494 --> 18:43.163
-Just wish one of my pieces had sold.
-Quite a scene.

18:44.123 --> 18:46.542
I don't think
I've ever seen you that way before.

18:46.625 --> 18:48.460
[pop song playing]

18:48.585 --> 18:50.838
Would have been nice to get an invitation.

18:51.672 --> 18:54.424
[chuckles] It wasn't about you.
It was about my work.

18:54.716 --> 18:57.136
Besides, you didn't seem to have
any problems getting in.

18:57.219 --> 18:59.138
-I'm Greer Childs.
-Mm, what a gift.

18:59.221 --> 19:02.724
I bet your other dudes were there.
Did they get an invitation?

19:02.808 --> 19:04.143
Yes, <i>she</i> did.

19:04.226 --> 19:06.311
I don't ask you about your other women.

19:06.395 --> 19:08.230
-[moaning]
-What do you want to know?

19:08.313 --> 19:11.024
-I don't.
-First time you sketched me...

19:12.442 --> 19:13.652
<i>what did you see?</i>

19:13.735 --> 19:17.573
[Nola] <i>Shapes, colors, lines.</i>

19:17.656 --> 19:22.035
Contrast, shadows, contours, and, uh...

19:23.203 --> 19:24.454
negative space.

19:29.376 --> 19:31.503
[line ringing]

19:34.339 --> 19:35.340
["Nola" playing]

20:00.741 --> 20:05.037
<i>♪ There's a girl that I once knew</i>
<i>Who often had a friend or two ♪</i>

20:05.120 --> 20:09.249
<i>♪ She gave them time</i>
<i>Love, wit, and rhyme, sublime ♪</i>

20:09.333 --> 20:13.545
<i>♪ They would come from far away</i>
<i>And often gather there all day ♪</i>

20:13.629 --> 20:17.257
<i>♪ To show their love</i>
<i>And see which one would stay ♪</i>

20:17.925 --> 20:22.095
<i>♪ But to her it mattered not</i>
<i>For loyalty was not her lot ♪</i>

20:22.179 --> 20:26.058
<i>♪ Her answer was</i>
<i>For not for them to know ♪</i>

20:26.391 --> 20:29.895
<i>♪ There she goes on her merry way ♪</i>

20:29.978 --> 20:34.566
<i>♪ Though she's only queen for a day ♪</i>

20:34.900 --> 20:38.820
<i>-♪ Boy and girl often take this world... ♪</i>
-Did I say you could sit down?

20:40.405 --> 20:41.615
Do I need permission?

20:42.157 --> 20:44.743
-Of course.
<i>-♪ My advice to you, my friend ♪</i>

20:44.826 --> 20:47.287
-[sighs]
<i>-♪ Is try to find what it's about ♪</i>

20:47.371 --> 20:51.458
<i>-♪ And then you take into account... ♪</i>
-Excuse me, miss, may I sit next to you?

20:52.084 --> 20:53.418
I love that song.

20:54.127 --> 20:55.629
Jay Z and Pharrell, right?

20:56.088 --> 20:57.631
What do you know about Hov?

20:57.714 --> 21:00.425
-I know he that dude.
-[chuckles]

21:00.801 --> 21:04.805
Did you know Jay Z mentions Rilke
in "What They Gonna Do"

21:04.888 --> 21:05.889
from <i>The Blueprint 2</i>?

21:06.682 --> 21:10.769
I have a friend of a friend who knows Jay,
who told me one of his dopest tracks,

21:10.852 --> 21:14.398
"There's Been a Murder," was heavily
influenced by Rilke's "Death Experience."

21:14.690 --> 21:15.691
You know that one?

21:16.400 --> 21:17.234
Naw.

21:18.694 --> 21:19.945
Spit a few bars.

21:21.947 --> 21:22.948
[chuckles]

21:24.700 --> 21:25.534
Okay.

21:28.120 --> 21:30.205
"We continue our play,

21:30.289 --> 21:32.708
picking up gestures now and then,

21:33.959 --> 21:39.339
and anxiously reciting
that which was difficult to learn.

21:40.507 --> 21:41.967
But you're far away

21:42.050 --> 21:45.095
so that, for a while,
we play life rapturously,

21:45.846 --> 21:47.681
not thinking of any applause."

21:49.558 --> 21:53.520
"Rapturously." Rilke was definitely
the Jay Z of his time.

21:56.231 --> 21:59.735
-So, I guess you like poetry or whatever.
-I love poetry.

22:03.405 --> 22:05.532
-My name is Jamie.
-Nola.

22:06.366 --> 22:09.828
-Pleased to meet you, Nola.
-Likewise, Mr. Jamie.

22:10.370 --> 22:13.373
Damn. "Mr. Jamie." It's like that?

22:13.832 --> 22:16.209
Yeah, it's like that. You grown as fuck.

22:16.293 --> 22:18.420
[both laughing]

22:18.879 --> 22:20.297
I love your candor.

22:20.380 --> 22:23.216
I love the fact
that you just used the word "candor."

22:23.800 --> 22:25.343
As opposed to "keepin' it 100"?

22:25.427 --> 22:29.765
Oh, my goodness. Everybody is saying
"keep it 100." Like, everybody.

22:29.848 --> 22:36.313
Especially the white hipsters,
trying to lean and dab around the pool

22:36.396 --> 22:40.942
at weekend rooftop parties
at the Gansevoort Park Avenue.

22:41.026 --> 22:44.196
It's a cultural black card. Plus,
they know all the words back-to-back.

22:44.279 --> 22:46.323
Of course they do. Drake is a cult.

22:47.407 --> 22:48.408
No doubt, Nola.

22:53.330 --> 22:54.873
But here's the burning question.

22:56.750 --> 22:57.584
What's that?

22:59.836 --> 23:01.880
Do you believe in love at first sight?

23:04.591 --> 23:07.094
In the film <i>Love Jones</i>, yes.

23:07.761 --> 23:10.931
<i>-♪ Now, it's time bid adieu ♪</i>
-Not so much in real life.

23:12.182 --> 23:16.269
<i>♪ I'll see you</i>
<i>When it's time to meet again ♪</i>

23:24.027 --> 23:25.445
[music ends]

23:25.529 --> 23:27.697
Nola, Jamie. Call me.

23:32.786 --> 23:34.955
-[pop music plays]
-In France, you don't enter the room

23:35.038 --> 23:37.624
wearing your race on your sleeve
like you do here.

23:37.707 --> 23:40.836
You know, you don't have to choose.
You can be both.

23:40.919 --> 23:45.674
So, when I came here as a kid,
it was a difficult transition.

23:45.757 --> 23:48.593
So, wait, what are you saying?
There's no racism in France?

23:48.677 --> 23:51.138
Do you see how the French
treat Africans and Muslims?

23:51.221 --> 23:55.892
I know. It's just more binary in the U.S.

23:56.810 --> 24:01.523
Anyway, so you're mad about some critic
who said that your work is pedestrian.

24:01.606 --> 24:02.524
Basically...

24:03.150 --> 24:07.237
I have no clear vision, and my work
didn't fit in with the theme of the show.

24:07.320 --> 24:09.656
Not cohesive, not black enough.

24:10.073 --> 24:12.951
You see, right there, a French critic
would never have that criticism.

24:13.034 --> 24:16.246
But, <i>chérie,</i>
you had very different pieces.

24:16.329 --> 24:19.749
Like, how do they actually... connect?

24:19.833 --> 24:21.001
They just do.

24:21.084 --> 24:24.379
Right, but I wanna know <i>how</i> they connect.

24:24.462 --> 24:26.840
How do you say "check, please"
in French, hm?

24:28.300 --> 24:30.552
Lilly? Lilly?

24:31.803 --> 24:33.680
[phone vibrating]

24:40.854 --> 24:44.441
Actually, your work
wasn't like the other artists.

24:44.858 --> 24:46.401
That's what I loved about it.

24:46.484 --> 24:50.864
Theirs was so blackity-black-black.
I'm so sick of that.

24:50.947 --> 24:54.242
And yours was... Nola's point of view.

24:55.118 --> 24:55.952
Fluid.

24:56.036 --> 24:59.122
Yes. Exactly. Thank you.

24:59.206 --> 25:01.458
This guy thinks
he's the authority on blackness,

25:01.541 --> 25:03.710
-the black female form.
-I love your form.

25:03.793 --> 25:05.587
And he's calling my blackness
into question

25:05.670 --> 25:07.797
as if there's some
singular representation,

25:07.881 --> 25:10.383
-like I'm not black enough.
-I completely understand.

25:10.467 --> 25:13.470
So, I get called out
by this white critic asshole

25:13.553 --> 25:16.306
for not expressing his version
of the black aesthetic?

25:16.389 --> 25:18.099
Like, what the fuck does he know?

25:18.183 --> 25:19.601
See? Thank you!

25:19.684 --> 25:22.854
That... That's what I'm trying to say.
We have so much in common.

25:22.938 --> 25:27.651
Like, how I get criticized by black people
for not being black enough.

25:27.734 --> 25:31.655
I feel like I'm always having to prove
my identity and choose a side.

25:31.738 --> 25:36.117
And if I choose, what?
Like, do I deny my white French mother?

25:36.201 --> 25:38.078
Does that make me more black?

25:38.161 --> 25:39.788
What about my African-American father?

25:39.871 --> 25:42.082
The man was a Black Panther,
for Christ's sake.

25:42.165 --> 25:43.750
It's just so fucked up.

25:43.833 --> 25:47.170
Commercially, the space is dominated
by white folks. They're the gatekeepers.

25:47.254 --> 25:49.673
They get to decide what's hot
and what's not.

25:50.840 --> 25:53.176
-[gasps]
-Can you feel how hard I am right now?

25:54.844 --> 25:56.012
[moans]

25:59.224 --> 26:01.977
But it's fucked up.
I just want you to be resilient.

26:02.686 --> 26:06.022
I love how you have the courage
to put your work out there.

26:07.482 --> 26:09.567
I want the same for myself, you know.

26:10.777 --> 26:14.114
Commercial photography is just disposable,
you know?

26:14.197 --> 26:15.782
It's just appeasing the clients.

26:15.865 --> 26:17.075
The gatekeepers.

26:17.158 --> 26:19.035
What are your artistic aspirations?

26:19.119 --> 26:24.666
I want my work to be immortal.
Maybe do a show. Put a book out.

26:24.749 --> 26:26.918
-You know, somethin' personal.
-Why don't you?

26:27.002 --> 26:28.461
It takes courage.

26:28.545 --> 26:31.923
I don't know, I guess I'm caught
between wantin' to move forward

26:32.007 --> 26:35.510
and wantin' to have the stability
of bein' able to eat.

26:35.719 --> 26:37.929
-[Nola chuckles]
-Keep a roof over my head.

26:39.347 --> 26:43.101
I don't wanna lose my net.
I mean, can't you see how I live?

26:43.184 --> 26:45.353
Sometimes, you gotta jump without the net.

26:45.437 --> 26:46.855
But I can understand that.

26:46.938 --> 26:50.400
You know,
that's that New York City hustle.

26:50.483 --> 26:53.111
Well, apparently not,
if your art's not selling.

26:54.321 --> 26:55.155
Wow!

26:55.989 --> 26:59.034
I was waiting for the old Greer
to rear its ugly-asshole head,

26:59.117 --> 27:00.118
and there it is.

27:00.201 --> 27:03.163
No, no, no, wait. <i>Chérie, </i>stay, sit.

27:04.039 --> 27:04.873
Relax.

27:12.297 --> 27:13.298
What are you doing?

27:14.215 --> 27:15.842
Why are you in <i>my </i>bathroom?

27:18.386 --> 27:19.387
Can I join you?

27:22.766 --> 27:23.600
Please?

27:26.102 --> 27:27.103
Shut the door.

27:31.941 --> 27:34.194
-[rap song playing]
<i>-♪ But I'll never change ♪</i>

27:34.277 --> 27:36.363
-You tryin' to trick me?
-[laughs]

27:36.446 --> 27:37.572
Here's your coat.

27:39.074 --> 27:40.700
-Oh, thank you...
-Of course.

27:40.784 --> 27:41.910
...for bringin' this.

27:43.620 --> 27:44.662
What's this?

27:47.415 --> 27:50.668
Really? Who are you today?

27:52.629 --> 27:53.630
[chuckles]

27:54.214 --> 27:55.423
Mm. This is pretty.

27:55.674 --> 27:59.260
<i>♪ How you gonna tell me what to do</i>
<i>How you gonna tell me who to be... ♪</i>

28:01.888 --> 28:03.932
That's so sweet.

28:04.015 --> 28:07.143
-You remember?
-Of course I remember.

28:07.227 --> 28:08.812
Yeah.

28:08.895 --> 28:13.566
I know the title's a bit shocking,
but it's actually a novel.

28:13.650 --> 28:17.070
It's about these two young
black roommates,

28:17.153 --> 28:20.907
these Francophiles livin' in the slums
of Montreal in the 1980s.

28:20.990 --> 28:22.367
-Mm-hm.
-So good.

28:22.450 --> 28:27.914
One's a writer, and the other sleeps a lot
and quotes the Quran and Camus.

28:27.997 --> 28:29.749
-[chuckles]
-They don't have much to do

28:29.833 --> 28:32.627
because all these white women
just keep throwing themselves at 'em.

28:32.710 --> 28:34.629
There <i>you</i> go.

28:34.712 --> 28:39.092
[in French accent] No, Miss Nola,
I don't want them. I want you.

28:39.676 --> 28:45.557
I want us to do this more. Go out, movies,
dates, together. What do you say?

28:46.766 --> 28:49.894
Um, I say I-I can't--
I can't do this right now.

28:51.896 --> 28:52.731
[Greer] Nola!

28:53.606 --> 28:56.276
Nola! Nola!

28:56.359 --> 29:00.697
Excuse me. Sorry. Excuse me.
Pardon me. Sorry.

29:01.448 --> 29:03.450
<i>-♪ I'll never change ♪</i>
-Excuse me. Sorry.

29:03.533 --> 29:05.952
<i>♪ You know I'll never ever change ♪</i>

29:10.832 --> 29:13.585
[playing "One For My Baby"]

29:23.261 --> 29:24.262
One more.

29:25.388 --> 29:27.098
<i>♪ It's quarter to three ♪</i>

29:29.100 --> 29:31.561
<i>♪ There's no one in the place ♪</i>

29:32.979 --> 29:34.981
<i>♪ Except you and me ♪</i>

29:39.861 --> 29:41.780
<i>♪ So, set 'em up, Joe ♪</i>

29:43.490 --> 29:45.325
<i>♪ I got a little story ♪</i>

29:45.408 --> 29:46.701
Thanks.

29:47.452 --> 29:50.789
<i>♪ I think you should know ♪</i>

29:53.833 --> 29:55.168
-Madame.
-Thank you.

29:55.251 --> 29:57.295
<i>-♪ We're drinking, my friend ♪</i>
-Vodka martini.

29:57.378 --> 30:00.882
-Thank you.
<i>-♪ To the end ♪</i>

30:00.965 --> 30:03.593
-Please, allow me.
-Oh, thank you.

30:09.015 --> 30:13.812
<i>♪ Make it one for my baby ♪</i>

30:14.938 --> 30:20.109
<i>♪ And one more for the road ♪</i>

30:25.865 --> 30:28.076
<i>♪ You'd never know it ♪</i>

30:28.159 --> 30:31.329
<i>♪ But, buddy, I'm a kind of poet ♪</i>

30:32.247 --> 30:38.294
<i>♪ And I got a lot of things</i>
<i>I'd like to say ♪</i>

30:40.129 --> 30:41.256
Like it?

30:41.339 --> 30:43.424
<i>♪ And when I'm gloomy ♪</i>

30:43.508 --> 30:45.552
[chuckles]

30:45.635 --> 30:48.680
<i>♪ Won't you listen to me? ♪</i>

30:52.100 --> 30:56.354
<i>♪ Till it's talked away ♪</i>

31:00.316 --> 31:05.655
<i>♪ Well, that's how it goes ♪</i>

31:07.198 --> 31:10.451
<i>♪ And, Joe, I know you're gettin' ♪</i>

31:11.661 --> 31:14.831
<i>♪ Anxious to close ♪</i>

31:15.081 --> 31:15.915
All right.

31:18.877 --> 31:21.629
<i>♪ And thanks for the cheer ♪</i>

31:23.131 --> 31:26.134
<i>♪ I hope you didn't mind ♪</i>

31:26.634 --> 31:30.763
<i>♪ My bendin' your ear ♪</i>

31:33.182 --> 31:37.687
<i>♪ But this torch that I found ♪</i>

31:38.229 --> 31:40.815
<i>♪ It's gotta be drowned ♪</i>

31:42.108 --> 31:46.446
<i>♪ Or it soon might explode ♪</i>

31:49.282 --> 31:53.536
<i>♪ So, make it one for my baby ♪</i>

31:55.872 --> 32:00.710
<i>♪ And one more for the road ♪</i>

32:02.712 --> 32:05.465
<i>♪ The long ♪</i>

32:08.176 --> 32:11.179
<i>♪ It's so long ♪</i>

32:12.764 --> 32:15.516
<i>♪ The long ♪</i>

32:17.060 --> 32:19.479
<i>♪ Very long ♪</i>

32:27.278 --> 32:29.948
[music ends]

32:33.952 --> 32:37.163
-[Joe] Hey, mac, I'm callin' you a cab.
-[Jamie] I miss you, Nola.

32:37.246 --> 32:38.081
[sighs]

32:38.831 --> 32:39.999
[grunts]

32:40.083 --> 32:41.876
[Jamie] <i>I miss you so much.</i>

32:43.127 --> 32:45.088
[machine beeping]

32:50.426 --> 32:51.719
Bitch, are you drunk?

32:52.804 --> 32:57.767
-What? No!
-Ah, shit. You're so loud.

32:57.850 --> 32:59.519
Shh! We're in a hospital.

33:01.896 --> 33:02.855
You look pretty.

33:03.439 --> 33:05.483
I feel like shit. [chuckles]

33:05.858 --> 33:07.068
You look like shit.

33:08.027 --> 33:10.947
-Damn you. I just like...
-[both laugh]

33:12.281 --> 33:13.533
[groaning]

33:13.616 --> 33:15.785
-Ow, shit.
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

33:19.706 --> 33:21.290
[voice quavers] I'm sorry.

33:23.918 --> 33:25.044
I'm sorry too.

33:29.298 --> 33:30.883
I'm sorry I missed your show.

33:34.887 --> 33:36.139
Sorry I missed yours too.

33:39.851 --> 33:41.227
You ain't miss anything.

33:42.603 --> 33:44.981
Neither did you, actually. [chuckles]

33:45.690 --> 33:49.986
[Shemekka sobbing]

33:51.070 --> 33:53.448
[soft piano music plays]
